Whirlpool to Increase Spending in Brazil by 30%, Estado Reports

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-05-07T14:28:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-07/whirlpool-to-increase-spending-in-brazil-by-30-estado-reports.html
Whirlpool Corp. (WHR)  will boost spending in
 Brazil  by as much as 30 percent this year,  O Estado de S. Paulo 
reported, citing an interview with Chairman and Chief Executive
Officer Jeff Fettig.  The appliance maker invested $180 million in the country in
2010, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in  Sao Paulo  at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  